Commentary Text: Chawla to Prithvi Shaw, out Stumped!! Chawla gets rid of both the openers in successive overs. Prithvi Shaw walks down the wicket to play the flatter delivery and gets outfoxed. Comes off an inside edge, rolls back off the pad towards Dhoni who had to lunge forward to get the ball and stretch to break the bails. No chance of getting back in and that's the end of an impressive innings by the Capitals' opener. Can CSK get a few more wickets and stem the flow of runs? Commentary Text: Axar to du Plessis, out Ruturaj Gaikwad Run Out!! This is the last thing CSK would've wanted at this stage. Needless. Patel lasers in the armer, du Plessis is cramped for room as he inside-edges it towards square leg. Ruturaj was keen to get to the other end as he races across the pitch only for Faf to send him back. Pant quickly sprints across and flings in a sharp throw to the bowler. He put in a full-length dive but wasn't enough. Axar cleanly breaks the stumps and he's a goner! Ruturaj Gaikwad run out (Pant/Axar) 5(10)

Vijay's painful stay at the crease comes to an end and has he played his last game for CSK? You never know. DC are a happy bunch. A simple back of a length delivery just outside off, some extra zip and pace did the trick for Nortje. Vijay just swung his bat, got it high on the bat and spooned a dolly to Rabada at mid-on. CSK two down and in a spot of bother. Vijay c Rabada b Nortje 10(15) [4s-1]

Commentary Text: Axar to Watson, out Caught by Hetmyer!! Watson walks straight into the trap set by Iyer and Co. For a second, I thought Hetmyer misjudged it by running in too far, but he keeps his calm and holds onto it. Another game, another instance of CSK losing an early wicket. Watson will be kicking himself there, couldn't have placed it any better. A short delivery begging to be hit, Watson jumped back and pulled it uppishly, didn't have the power to clear the fielder at deep mid-wicket. Very poor.. Patel is pumped.
